We gushed over the Wachowskisâ€™ vision and scope for action set pieces, the multitude of philosophical references found in the movies, their alleged self-indulgence, cultural footprint and much, much more. If you're operating on its wavelength, it frequently offers some of the most dazzling digital scenery ever. What would the biblical battle of tomorrow look like? Behemoths forged out of wrought iron, tickled incessantly by the machines' voltaic lifeblood. A blind Neo making pilgrimage, escorted by little worker bots, finding something beautiful to see even within his enemies. The future will be driven, not dictated by our capability to choose peace over war and vice versa.

The Matrix is noir, Reloaded is a heist flick, and our final entry is a knotty combination of horror and war, balancing the two almost as well as the legendary Aliens. I really explained it best last time, so todayâ€¦
